The paper addresses the problem of object localisation in images, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework is based on Bayesian modelling, which involves probabilistic inference and learning (cs.LG). The model integrates prior knowledge about object appearance, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of weak labels, which is a topic in natural language processing and text classification (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments involve the use of a dataset, which is a common theme in multimedia and information retrieval (cs.MM).
